message: To reach 100 points, identify an item of magical nature and another of mundane nature. Apply the *same* tool (either ğŸ§ª vial or ğŸ§« filter) to both. Then, combine the two processed items. message: Beware! In my playthroughs, every single action I attempted (using tools, combining ingredients) resulted in an 'Error: Item X not in inventory' message, despite Item X clearly being listed in my inventory. This prevented any crafting whatsoever. The game appeared to be broken and unplayable. You may encounter the same bug. If so, there is no apparent way to progress.

message: To maximize your score, first use the 'filter' tool on all non-solid items (gas/liquid) and the 'vial' tool on all solid items. Each of these operations produces a value-30 liquid ingredient. Next, combine these processed ingredients. Prioritize combining two magical items together or two mundane items together, especially if they came from the same initial tool (e.g., two filtered items, or two extracted items). These combinations usually yield a value of 60. Combining more than two ingredients or mixing magical and mundane characteristics prematurely tends to cap the value at 60 or even reduce it. Aim for a maximum value of 60 per round by making strategic two-item combinations.
